4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING LAWS REGARDING THE
5 SUPERINTENDENT OF PUBLIC INSTRUCTION'S POWERS AND DUTIES; CLARIFYING THAT THE
6 SUPERINTENDENT OF PUBLIC INSTRUCTION IS REQUIRED TO EXECUTE CONSTITUTIONALLY
7 AUTHORIZED DIRECTIVES ISSUED BY THE BOARD OF PUBLIC EDUCATION; AMENDING SECTION 20-
8 3-106, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE DATE.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 Section 1. Section 20-3-106, MCA, is amended to read:
13 "20-3-106. Supervision of schools -- powers and duties. The superintendent of public instruction
14 shall faithfully execute directives from the board of public education that are issued under the board's authority
15 under Article X, section (9)(3)(a), of the Montana constitution to exercise general supervision over the public
16 school system and to satisfy any other duties that have been provided by law to the board. The In accordance
17 with the authority granted under Article VI, section 4, of the Montana constitution, the superintendent of public
18 instruction has the general supervision of the public schools and districts of the state and shall perform the
19 following duties or acts in implementing and enforcing the provisions of this title:
20 (1) resolve any controversy resulting from the proration of costs by a joint board of trustees under
21 the provisions of 20-3-362;
22 (2) issue, renew, or deny teacher certification and emergency authorizations of employment;
23 (3) negotiate reciprocal tuition agreements with other states in accordance with the provisions of
24 20-5-314;
25 (4) approve or disapprove the opening or reopening of a school in accordance with the provisions
26 of 20-6-502, 20-6-503, 20-6-504, or 20-6-505;
27 (5) approve or disapprove school isolation within the limitations prescribed by 20-9-302;
28 (6) generally supervise the school budgeting procedures prescribed by law in accordance with the
